  "body": "*Title*: *Changing endpoint priority causes Envoy to lose track of the endpoint*\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nWhen moving an endpoint to a new priority, Envoy loses track of that endpoint.\r\n\r\nExample before and after eds config:\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n```\r\nresources:\r\n- \"@type\": type.googleapis.com/envoy.api.v2.ClusterLoadAssignment\r\n  cluster_name: service1\r\n  endpoints:\r\n  - lb_endpoints:\r\n      - endpoint:\r\n          address:\r\n            socket_address:\r\n              address: {{service1_1_ip}}\r\n              port_value: 80\r\n      - endpoint:\r\n          address:\r\n            socket_address:\r\n              address: {{service1_2_ip}}\r\n              port_value: 80\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n```\r\nresources:\r\n- \"@type\": type.googleapis.com/envoy.api.v2.ClusterLoadAssignment\r\n  cluster_name: service1\r\n  endpoints:\r\n  - priority: 0\r\n    lb_endpoints:\r\n      - endpoint:\r\n          address:\r\n            socket_address:\r\n              address: {{service1_1_ip}}\r\n              port_value: 80\r\n  - priority: 1\r\n    lb_endpoints:\r\n      - endpoint:\r\n          address:\r\n            socket_address:\r\n              address: {{service1_2_ip}}\r\n              port_value: 80\r\n```\r\n\r\nEnvoy will no longer know about `{{service1_2_ip}}`\r\n\r\n*Repro steps*:\r\nI've created a repro here: https://github.com/bplotnick/envoy_examples/tree/master/losing_endpoints\r\n\r\nCC: @mpuncel and @snowp who dealt with something similar in #3930",
